INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Altbier','hops','Grists vary, but usually consist of German base malts \(usually Pils, sometimes Munich\) with small amounts of crystal, chocolate, and/or black malts used to adjust color. Occasionally will include some wheat, including roasted wheat. Spalt hops are traditional, but other Saazer\-type hops can also be used. Clean, highly attenuative ale yeast. A step mash or decoction mash program is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Altbier','malt','Grists vary, but usually consist of German base malts \(usually Pils, sometimes Munich\) with small amounts of crystal, chocolate, and/or black malts used to adjust color. Occasionally will include some wheat, including roasted wheat. Spalt hops are traditional, but other Saazer\-type hops can also be used. Clean, highly attenuative ale yeast. A step mash or decoction mash program is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Altbier','wheat','Grists vary, but usually consist of German base malts \(usually Pils, sometimes Munich\) with small amounts of crystal, chocolate, and/or black malts used to adjust color. Occasionally will include some wheat, including roasted wheat. Spalt hops are traditional, but other Saazer\-type hops can also be used. Clean, highly attenuative ale yeast. A step mash or decoction mash program is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Altbier','yeast','Grists vary, but usually consist of German base malts \(usually Pils, sometimes Munich\) with small amounts of crystal, chocolate, and/or black malts used to adjust color. Occasionally will include some wheat, including roasted wheat. Spalt hops are traditional, but other Saazer\-type hops can also be used. Clean, highly attenuative ale yeast. A step mash or decoction mash program is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Amber Ale','hops','Pale ale malt, typically North American two\-row. Medium to dark crystal malts. May also contain specialty grains which add additional character and uniqueness. American or New World hops, often with citrusy flavors, are common but others may also be used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Amber Ale','malt','Pale ale malt, typically North American two\-row. Medium to dark crystal malts. May also contain specialty grains which add additional character and uniqueness. American or New World hops, often with citrusy flavors, are common but others may also be used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Barleywine','hops','Well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist. Some specialty or character malts may be used. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. New World hops are common, although any varieties can be used in quantity. Generally uses an attenuative American ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Barleywine','malt','Well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist. Some specialty or character malts may be used. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. New World hops are common, although any varieties can be used in quantity. Generally uses an attenuative American ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Barleywine','yeast','Well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist. Some specialty or character malts may be used. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. New World hops are common, although any varieties can be used in quantity. Generally uses an attenuative American ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Brown Ale','hops','Well\-modified pale malt, plus crystal and darker malts \(typically chocolate\). American hops are typical, but continental or New World hops can also be used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Brown Ale','malt','Well\-modified pale malt, plus crystal and darker malts \(typically chocolate\). American hops are typical, but continental or New World hops can also be used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American IPA','hops','Pale ale or 2\-row brewers malt as the base, American or New World hops, American or English yeast with a clean or slightly fruity profile. Generally all\-malt, but mashed at lower temperatures for high attenuation. Sugar additions to aid attenuation are acceptable. Restrained use of crystal malts, if any, as high amounts can lead to a sweet finish and clash with the hop character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American IPA','malt','Pale ale or 2\-row brewers malt as the base, American or New World hops, American or English yeast with a clean or slightly fruity profile. Generally all\-malt, but mashed at lower temperatures for high attenuation. Sugar additions to aid attenuation are acceptable. Restrained use of crystal malts, if any, as high amounts can lead to a sweet finish and clash with the hop character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American IPA','yeast','Pale ale or 2\-row brewers malt as the base, American or New World hops, American or English yeast with a clean or slightly fruity profile. Generally all\-malt, but mashed at lower temperatures for high attenuation. Sugar additions to aid attenuation are acceptable. Restrained use of crystal malts, if any, as high amounts can lead to a sweet finish and clash with the hop character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Lager','corn','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Lager','rice','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Lager','six\-row barley','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Light Lager','corn','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts. Additional enzymes can further lighten the body and lower carbohydrates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Light Lager','rice','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts. Additional enzymes can further lighten the body and lower carbohydrates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Light Lager','six\-row barley','Two\- or six\-row barley with high percentage \(up to 40\%\) of rice or corn as adjuncts. Additional enzymes can further lighten the body and lower carbohydrates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Pale Ale','hops','Pale ale malt, typically North American two\-row. American or New World hops, with a wide range of allowable characteristics. American or English ale yeast \(neutral to lightly fruity\). Specialty grains may add character and complexity, but generally make up a relatively small portion of the grist. Grains that add malt flavor and richness, light sweetness, and toasty or bready notes are often used \(along with late hops\) to differentiate brands.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Pale Ale','malt','Pale ale malt, typically North American two\-row. American or New World hops, with a wide range of allowable characteristics. American or English ale yeast \(neutral to lightly fruity\). Specialty grains may add character and complexity, but generally make up a relatively small portion of the grist. Grains that add malt flavor and richness, light sweetness, and toasty or bready notes are often used \(along with late hops\) to differentiate brands.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Pale Ale','yeast','Pale ale malt, typically North American two\-row. American or New World hops, with a wide range of allowable characteristics. American or English ale yeast \(neutral to lightly fruity\). Specialty grains may add character and complexity, but generally make up a relatively small portion of the grist. Grains that add malt flavor and richness, light sweetness, and toasty or bready notes are often used \(along with late hops\) to differentiate brands.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Porter','hops','May contain several malts, prominently dark malts, which often include black malt \(chocolate malt is also often used\). American hops typically used for bittering, but US or UK finishing hops can be used; a clashing citrus quality is generally undesirable. Ale yeast can either be clean US versions or characterful English varieties.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Porter','malt','May contain several malts, prominently dark malts, which often include black malt \(chocolate malt is also often used\). American hops typically used for bittering, but US or UK finishing hops can be used; a clashing citrus quality is generally undesirable. Ale yeast can either be clean US versions or characterful English varieties.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Porter','yeast','May contain several malts, prominently dark malts, which often include black malt \(chocolate malt is also often used\). American hops typically used for bittering, but US or UK finishing hops can be used; a clashing citrus quality is generally undesirable. Ale yeast can either be clean US versions or characterful English varieties.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Stout','malt','Common American base malts and yeast. Varied use of dark and roasted malts, as well as caramel\-type malts. Adjuncts such as oatmeal may be present in low quantities. American hop varieties.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Stout','yeast','Common American base malts and yeast. Varied use of dark and roasted malts, as well as caramel\-type malts. Adjuncts such as oatmeal may be present in low quantities. American hop varieties.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Strong Ale','hops','Well\-modified pale malt as a base; some character malts would be appropriate, medium to dark crystal malts are typical. Citrusy or piney American hops are common, although any American or New World varieties can be used in quantity, provided they do not clash with the malt character. Generally uses an attenuative American yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Strong Ale','malt','Well\-modified pale malt as a base; some character malts would be appropriate, medium to dark crystal malts are typical. Citrusy or piney American hops are common, although any American or New World varieties can be used in quantity, provided they do not clash with the malt character. Generally uses an attenuative American yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Strong Ale','yeast','Well\-modified pale malt as a base; some character malts would be appropriate, medium to dark crystal malts are typical. Citrusy or piney American hops are common, although any American or New World varieties can be used in quantity, provided they do not clash with the malt character. Generally uses an attenuative American yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Wheat Beer','hops','Clean American ale or lager yeast \(German weissbier yeast is inappropriate\). Large proportion of wheat malt \(often 30–50\%, which is lower than is typical in German weissbiers\). American, German, or New World hops are typical.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Wheat Beer','malt','Clean American ale or lager yeast \(German weissbier yeast is inappropriate\). Large proportion of wheat malt \(often 30–50\%, which is lower than is typical in German weissbiers\). American, German, or New World hops are typical.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Wheat Beer','wheat','Clean American ale or lager yeast \(German weissbier yeast is inappropriate\). Large proportion of wheat malt \(often 30–50\%, which is lower than is typical in German weissbiers\). American, German, or New World hops are typical.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('American Wheat Beer','yeast','Clean American ale or lager yeast \(German weissbier yeast is inappropriate\). Large proportion of wheat malt \(often 30–50\%, which is lower than is typical in German weissbiers\). American, German, or New World hops are typical.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Australian Sparkling Ale','hops','Lightly kilned Australian 2\-row pale malt, lager varieties may be used. Small amounts of crystal malt for color adjustment only. Modern examples use no adjuncts, cane sugar for priming only. Historical examples using 45\% 2 row, 30\% higher protein malt \(6 row\) would use around 25\% sugar to dilute the nitrogen content. Traditionally used Australian hops, Cluster, and Goldings until replaced from mid\-1960s by Pride of Ringwood. Highly attenuative Burton\-type yeast \(Australian\-type strain typical\). Variable water profile, typically with low carbonate and moderate sulfate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Australian Sparkling Ale','malt','Lightly kilned Australian 2\-row pale malt, lager varieties may be used. Small amounts of crystal malt for color adjustment only. Modern examples use no adjuncts, cane sugar for priming only. Historical examples using 45\% 2 row, 30\% higher protein malt \(6 row\) would use around 25\% sugar to dilute the nitrogen content. Traditionally used Australian hops, Cluster, and Goldings until replaced from mid\-1960s by Pride of Ringwood. Highly attenuative Burton\-type yeast \(Australian\-type strain typical\). Variable water profile, typically with low carbonate and moderate sulfate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Australian Sparkling Ale','sugar','Lightly kilned Australian 2\-row pale malt, lager varieties may be used. Small amounts of crystal malt for color adjustment only. Modern examples use no adjuncts, cane sugar for priming only. Historical examples using 45\% 2 row, 30\% higher protein malt \(6 row\) would use around 25\% sugar to dilute the nitrogen content. Traditionally used Australian hops, Cluster, and Goldings until replaced from mid\-1960s by Pride of Ringwood. Highly attenuative Burton\-type yeast \(Australian\-type strain typical\). Variable water profile, typically with low carbonate and moderate sulfate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Australian Sparkling Ale','yeast','Lightly kilned Australian 2\-row pale malt, lager varieties may be used. Small amounts of crystal malt for color adjustment only. Modern examples use no adjuncts, cane sugar for priming only. Historical examples using 45\% 2 row, 30\% higher protein malt \(6 row\) would use around 25\% sugar to dilute the nitrogen content. Traditionally used Australian hops, Cluster, and Goldings until replaced from mid\-1960s by Pride of Ringwood. Highly attenuative Burton\-type yeast \(Australian\-type strain typical\). Variable water profile, typically with low carbonate and moderate sulfate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Autumn Seasonal Beer','sugar','Spices are required, and often include those evocative of the fall or Thanksgiving season \(e.g., allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves, ginger\) but any combination is possible and creativity is encouraged. Flavorful adjuncts are often used \(e.g., molasses, invert sugar, brown sugar, honey, maple syrup, etc.\). Squash\-type or gourd\-type vegetables \(most frequently pumpkin\) are often used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Baltic Porter','hops','Generally lager yeast \(cold fermented if using ale yeast, as is required when brewed in Russia\). Debittered chocolate or black malt. Munich or Vienna base malt. Continental hops \(Saazer\-type, typically\). May contain crystal malts and/or adjuncts. Brown or amber malt common in historical recipes.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Baltic Porter','malt','Generally lager yeast \(cold fermented if using ale yeast, as is required when brewed in Russia\). Debittered chocolate or black malt. Munich or Vienna base malt. Continental hops \(Saazer\-type, typically\). May contain crystal malts and/or adjuncts. Brown or amber malt common in historical recipes.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Baltic Porter','yeast','Generally lager yeast \(cold fermented if using ale yeast, as is required when brewed in Russia\). Debittered chocolate or black malt. Munich or Vienna base malt. Continental hops \(Saazer\-type, typically\). May contain crystal malts and/or adjuncts. Brown or amber malt common in historical recipes.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Blond Ale','hops','Belgian Pils malt, aromatic malts, sugar, Belgian yeast strains that produce complex alcohol, phenolics and perfumy esters, Saazer\-type, Styrian Goldings, or East Kent Goldings hops. Spices are not traditionally used, although the ingredients and fermentation by\-products may give an impression of spicing \(often reminiscent of oranges or lemons\). If spices are present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Blond Ale','malt','Belgian Pils malt, aromatic malts, sugar, Belgian yeast strains that produce complex alcohol, phenolics and perfumy esters, Saazer\-type, Styrian Goldings, or East Kent Goldings hops. Spices are not traditionally used, although the ingredients and fermentation by\-products may give an impression of spicing \(often reminiscent of oranges or lemons\). If spices are present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Blond Ale','spices','Belgian Pils malt, aromatic malts, sugar, Belgian yeast strains that produce complex alcohol, phenolics and perfumy esters, Saazer\-type, Styrian Goldings, or East Kent Goldings hops. Spices are not traditionally used, although the ingredients and fermentation by\-products may give an impression of spicing \(often reminiscent of oranges or lemons\). If spices are present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Blond Ale','sugar','Belgian Pils malt, aromatic malts, sugar, Belgian yeast strains that produce complex alcohol, phenolics and perfumy esters, Saazer\-type, Styrian Goldings, or East Kent Goldings hops. Spices are not traditionally used, although the ingredients and fermentation by\-products may give an impression of spicing \(often reminiscent of oranges or lemons\). If spices are present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Blond Ale','yeast','Belgian Pils malt, aromatic malts, sugar, Belgian yeast strains that produce complex alcohol, phenolics and perfumy esters, Saazer\-type, Styrian Goldings, or East Kent Goldings hops. Spices are not traditionally used, although the ingredients and fermentation by\-products may give an impression of spicing \(often reminiscent of oranges or lemons\). If spices are present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dark Strong Ale','hops','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and sometimes phenolics are commonly used. Impression of a complex grain bill, although many traditional versions are quite simple, with caramelized sugar syrup or unrefined sugars and yeast providing much of the complexity. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. Spices generally not used; if used, keep subtle and in the background.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dark Strong Ale','sugar','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and sometimes phenolics are commonly used. Impression of a complex grain bill, although many traditional versions are quite simple, with caramelized sugar syrup or unrefined sugars and yeast providing much of the complexity. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. Spices generally not used; if used, keep subtle and in the background.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dark Strong Ale','yeast','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and sometimes phenolics are commonly used. Impression of a complex grain bill, although many traditional versions are quite simple, with caramelized sugar syrup or unrefined sugars and yeast providing much of the complexity. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. Spices generally not used; if used, keep subtle and in the background.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dubbel','hops','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and phenolics are commonly used. Impression of complex grain bill, although traditional versions are typically Belgian Pils malt with caramelized sugar syrup or other unrefined sugars providing much of the character. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. No spices are traditionally used, although restrained use is allowable \(background strength only\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dubbel','malt','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and phenolics are commonly used. Impression of complex grain bill, although traditional versions are typically Belgian Pils malt with caramelized sugar syrup or other unrefined sugars providing much of the character. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. No spices are traditionally used, although restrained use is allowable \(background strength only\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dubbel','spices','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and phenolics are commonly used. Impression of complex grain bill, although traditional versions are typically Belgian Pils malt with caramelized sugar syrup or other unrefined sugars providing much of the character. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. No spices are traditionally used, although restrained use is allowable \(background strength only\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dubbel','sugar','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and phenolics are commonly used. Impression of complex grain bill, although traditional versions are typically Belgian Pils malt with caramelized sugar syrup or other unrefined sugars providing much of the character. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. No spices are traditionally used, although restrained use is allowable \(background strength only\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Dubbel','yeast','Belgian yeast strains prone to production of higher alcohols, esters, and phenolics are commonly used. Impression of complex grain bill, although traditional versions are typically Belgian Pils malt with caramelized sugar syrup or other unrefined sugars providing much of the character. Saazer\-type, English\-type or Styrian Goldings hops commonly used. No spices are traditionally used, although restrained use is allowable \(background strength only\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Golden Strong Ale','hops','Pilsner malt with substantial sugary adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Fairly soft water. Spicing is not traditional; if present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Golden Strong Ale','malt','Pilsner malt with substantial sugary adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Fairly soft water. Spicing is not traditional; if present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Golden Strong Ale','sugar','Pilsner malt with substantial sugary adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Fairly soft water. Spicing is not traditional; if present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Golden Strong Ale','yeast','Pilsner malt with substantial sugary adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Fairly soft water. Spicing is not traditional; if present, should be a background character only.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Pale Ale','hops','Pilsner or pale ale malt contributes the bulk of the grist with \(cara\) Vienna and Munich malts adding color, body and complexity. Sugar is not commonly used as high gravity is not desired. Saazer\-type hops, Styrian Goldings, East Kent Goldings or Fuggles are commonly used. Yeasts prone to moderate production of phenols are often used but fermentation temperatures should be kept moderate to limit this character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Pale Ale','malt','Pilsner or pale ale malt contributes the bulk of the grist with \(cara\) Vienna and Munich malts adding color, body and complexity. Sugar is not commonly used as high gravity is not desired. Saazer\-type hops, Styrian Goldings, East Kent Goldings or Fuggles are commonly used. Yeasts prone to moderate production of phenols are often used but fermentation temperatures should be kept moderate to limit this character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Tripel','hops','Pilsner malt, typically with pale sugar adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Spice additions are generally not traditional, and if used, should be a background character only. Fairly soft water.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Tripel','malt','Pilsner malt, typically with pale sugar adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Spice additions are generally not traditional, and if used, should be a background character only. Fairly soft water.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Tripel','sugar','Pilsner malt, typically with pale sugar adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Spice additions are generally not traditional, and if used, should be a background character only. Fairly soft water.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Belgian Tripel','yeast','Pilsner malt, typically with pale sugar adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops or Styrian Goldings are commonly used. Belgian yeast strains are used – those that produce fruity esters, spicy phenolics and higher alcohols – often aided by slightly warmer fermentation temperatures. Spice additions are generally not traditional, and if used, should be a background character only. Fairly soft water.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Berliner Weisse','malt','Wheat malt content is typically 50\% of the grist \(as is tradition with all German wheat beers\) with the remainder typically being Pilsner malt. A symbiotic fermentation with top\-fermenting yeast and Lactobacillus \(various strains\) provides the sharp sourness, which may be enhanced by blending of beers of different ages during fermentation and by extended cool aging. Hop bitterness is non\-existent. Decoction mashing with mash hopping is traditional. German brewing scientists believe that Brettanomyces is essential to get the correct flavor profile, but this character is never strong.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Berliner Weisse','wheat','Wheat malt content is typically 50\% of the grist \(as is tradition with all German wheat beers\) with the remainder typically being Pilsner malt. A symbiotic fermentation with top\-fermenting yeast and Lactobacillus \(various strains\) provides the sharp sourness, which may be enhanced by blending of beers of different ages during fermentation and by extended cool aging. Hop bitterness is non\-existent. Decoction mashing with mash hopping is traditional. German brewing scientists believe that Brettanomyces is essential to get the correct flavor profile, but this character is never strong.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Berliner Weisse','yeast','Wheat malt content is typically 50\% of the grist \(as is tradition with all German wheat beers\) with the remainder typically being Pilsner malt. A symbiotic fermentation with top\-fermenting yeast and Lactobacillus \(various strains\) provides the sharp sourness, which may be enhanced by blending of beers of different ages during fermentation and by extended cool aging. Hop bitterness is non\-existent. Decoction mashing with mash hopping is traditional. German brewing scientists believe that Brettanomyces is essential to get the correct flavor profile, but this character is never strong.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Best Bitter','corn','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Best Bitter','hops','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
