INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Bière de Garde','hops','The "cellar" character commonly described in literature is more of a feature of mishandled commercial exports than fresh, authentic products. The somewhat moldy character comes from the corks and/or oxidation in commercial versions, and is incorrectly identified as "musty" or "cellar\-like." Base malts vary by beer color, but usually include pale, Vienna and Munich types. Darker versions will have richer malt complexity and sweetness from crystal\-type malts. Sugar may be used to add flavor and aid in the dry finish. Lager or ale yeast fermented at cool ale temperatures, followed by long cold conditioning. Floral, herbal or spicy continental hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Bière de Garde','malt','The "cellar" character commonly described in literature is more of a feature of mishandled commercial exports than fresh, authentic products. The somewhat moldy character comes from the corks and/or oxidation in commercial versions, and is incorrectly identified as "musty" or "cellar\-like." Base malts vary by beer color, but usually include pale, Vienna and Munich types. Darker versions will have richer malt complexity and sweetness from crystal\-type malts. Sugar may be used to add flavor and aid in the dry finish. Lager or ale yeast fermented at cool ale temperatures, followed by long cold conditioning. Floral, herbal or spicy continental hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Bière de Garde','yeast','The "cellar" character commonly described in literature is more of a feature of mishandled commercial exports than fresh, authentic products. The somewhat moldy character comes from the corks and/or oxidation in commercial versions, and is incorrectly identified as "musty" or "cellar\-like." Base malts vary by beer color, but usually include pale, Vienna and Munich types. Darker versions will have richer malt complexity and sweetness from crystal\-type malts. Sugar may be used to add flavor and aid in the dry finish. Lager or ale yeast fermented at cool ale temperatures, followed by long cold conditioning. Floral, herbal or spicy continental hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Blonde Ale','malt','Generally all malt, but can include up to 25\% wheat malt and some sugar adjuncts. Any hop variety can be used. Clean American, lightly fruity English, or Kölsch yeast. May also be made with lager yeast, or cold\-conditioned. Some versions may have honey, spices and/or fruit added, although if any of these ingredients are stronger than a background flavor they should be entered in those specialty categories instead.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Blonde Ale','spices','Generally all malt, but can include up to 25\% wheat malt and some sugar adjuncts. Any hop variety can be used. Clean American, lightly fruity English, or Kölsch yeast. May also be made with lager yeast, or cold\-conditioned. Some versions may have honey, spices and/or fruit added, although if any of these ingredients are stronger than a background flavor they should be entered in those specialty categories instead.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Blonde Ale','sugar','Generally all malt, but can include up to 25\% wheat malt and some sugar adjuncts. Any hop variety can be used. Clean American, lightly fruity English, or Kölsch yeast. May also be made with lager yeast, or cold\-conditioned. Some versions may have honey, spices and/or fruit added, although if any of these ingredients are stronger than a background flavor they should be entered in those specialty categories instead.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Blonde Ale','wheat','Generally all malt, but can include up to 25\% wheat malt and some sugar adjuncts. Any hop variety can be used. Clean American, lightly fruity English, or Kölsch yeast. May also be made with lager yeast, or cold\-conditioned. Some versions may have honey, spices and/or fruit added, although if any of these ingredients are stronger than a background flavor they should be entered in those specialty categories instead.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Blonde Ale','yeast','Generally all malt, but can include up to 25\% wheat malt and some sugar adjuncts. Any hop variety can be used. Clean American, lightly fruity English, or Kölsch yeast. May also be made with lager yeast, or cold\-conditioned. Some versions may have honey, spices and/or fruit added, although if any of these ingredients are stronger than a background flavor they should be entered in those specialty categories instead.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Brown Ale','malt','British mild ale or pale ale malt base with caramel malts. May also have small amounts darker malts \(e.g., chocolate\) to provide color and the nutty character. English hop varieties are most authentic.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','corn','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','hops','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','malt','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','sugar','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','wheat','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Golden Ale','yeast','Low\-color pale or lager malt acting as a blank canvas for the hop character. May use sugar adjuncts, corn or wheat. English hops frequently used, although citrusy American varietals are becoming more common. Somewhat clean\-fermenting British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Strong Ale','hops','Grists vary, often based on pale malt with caramel and specialty malts. Some darker examples suggest that dark malts \(e.g., chocolate, black malt\) may be appropriate, though sparingly so as to avoid an overly roasted character. Sugary adjuncts are common, as are starchy adjuncts \(maize, flaked barley, wheat\). Finishing hops are traditionally English.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Strong Ale','malt','Grists vary, often based on pale malt with caramel and specialty malts. Some darker examples suggest that dark malts \(e.g., chocolate, black malt\) may be appropriate, though sparingly so as to avoid an overly roasted character. Sugary adjuncts are common, as are starchy adjuncts \(maize, flaked barley, wheat\). Finishing hops are traditionally English.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('British Strong Ale','wheat','Grists vary, often based on pale malt with caramel and specialty malts. Some darker examples suggest that dark malts \(e.g., chocolate, black malt\) may be appropriate, though sparingly so as to avoid an overly roasted character. Sugary adjuncts are common, as are starchy adjuncts \(maize, flaked barley, wheat\). Finishing hops are traditionally English.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('California Common','hops','Pale ale malt, non\-citrusy hops \(often Northern Brewer\), small amounts of toasted malt and/or crystal malts. Lager yeast; however, some strains \(often with the mention of "California" in the name\) work better than others at the warmer fermentation temperatures \(55 to 60 °F\) typically used. Note that some German yeast strains produce inappropriate sulfury character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('California Common','malt','Pale ale malt, non\-citrusy hops \(often Northern Brewer\), small amounts of toasted malt and/or crystal malts. Lager yeast; however, some strains \(often with the mention of "California" in the name\) work better than others at the warmer fermentation temperatures \(55 to 60 °F\) typically used. Note that some German yeast strains produce inappropriate sulfury character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('California Common','yeast','Pale ale malt, non\-citrusy hops \(often Northern Brewer\), small amounts of toasted malt and/or crystal malts. Lager yeast; however, some strains \(often with the mention of "California" in the name\) work better than others at the warmer fermentation temperatures \(55 to 60 °F\) typically used. Note that some German yeast strains produce inappropriate sulfury character.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Classic Style Smoked Beer','malt','Different materials used to smoke malt result in unique flavor and aroma characteristics. Beechwood, or other hardwood \(oak, maple, mesquite, alder, pecan, apple, cherry, other fruitwoods\) smoked malts may be used. The various woods may remind one of certain smoked products due to their food association \(e.g., hickory with ribs, maple with bacon or sausage, and alder with salmon\). Evergreen wood should never be used since it adds a medicinal, piney flavor to the malt. Noticeable peat\-smoked malt is universally undesirable due to its sharp, piercing phenolics and dirt\-like earthiness. The remaining ingredients vary with the base style. If smoked malts are combined with other unusual ingredients \(fruits, vegetables, spices, honey, etc.\) in noticeable quantities, the resulting beer should be entered in the Specialty Smoked Beer.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Classic Style Smoked Beer','spices','Different materials used to smoke malt result in unique flavor and aroma characteristics. Beechwood, or other hardwood \(oak, maple, mesquite, alder, pecan, apple, cherry, other fruitwoods\) smoked malts may be used. The various woods may remind one of certain smoked products due to their food association \(e.g., hickory with ribs, maple with bacon or sausage, and alder with salmon\). Evergreen wood should never be used since it adds a medicinal, piney flavor to the malt. Noticeable peat\-smoked malt is universally undesirable due to its sharp, piercing phenolics and dirt\-like earthiness. The remaining ingredients vary with the base style. If smoked malts are combined with other unusual ingredients \(fruits, vegetables, spices, honey, etc.\) in noticeable quantities, the resulting beer should be entered in the Specialty Smoked Beer.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Cream Ale','hops','American ingredients most commonly used. A grain bill of six\-row malt, or a combination of six\-row and North American two\-row, is common. Adjuncts can include up to 20\% maize in the mash, and up to 20\% glucose or other sugars in the boil. Any variety of hops can be used for bittering and finishing.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Cream Ale','malt','American ingredients most commonly used. A grain bill of six\-row malt, or a combination of six\-row and North American two\-row, is common. Adjuncts can include up to 20\% maize in the mash, and up to 20\% glucose or other sugars in the boil. Any variety of hops can be used for bittering and finishing.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Cream Ale','sugar','American ingredients most commonly used. A grain bill of six\-row malt, or a combination of six\-row and North American two\-row, is common. Adjuncts can include up to 20\% maize in the mash, and up to 20\% glucose or other sugars in the boil. Any variety of hops can be used for bittering and finishing.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Amber Lager','hops','Pilsner and caramel malts, but Vienna and Munich malts may also be used. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Amber Lager','malt','Pilsner and caramel malts, but Vienna and Munich malts may also be used. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Amber Lager','yeast','Pilsner and caramel malts, but Vienna and Munich malts may also be used. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Dark Lager','hops','Pilsner and dark caramel malts with the addition of debittered roasted malts are most common, but additions of Vienna or Munich malt are also appropriate. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast. Any fruity esters are typically from malt, not yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Dark Lager','malt','Pilsner and dark caramel malts with the addition of debittered roasted malts are most common, but additions of Vienna or Munich malt are also appropriate. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast. Any fruity esters are typically from malt, not yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Dark Lager','yeast','Pilsner and dark caramel malts with the addition of debittered roasted malts are most common, but additions of Vienna or Munich malt are also appropriate. Low mineral content water, Saazer\-type hops, Czech lager yeast. Any fruity esters are typically from malt, not yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Pale Lager','hops','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech Pilsner malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Pale Lager','malt','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech Pilsner malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Pale Lager','yeast','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech Pilsner malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Premium Pale Lager','hops','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates. The bitterness level of some larger commercial examples has dropped in recent years, although not as much as in many contemporary German examples.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Premium Pale Lager','malt','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates. The bitterness level of some larger commercial examples has dropped in recent years, although not as much as in many contemporary German examples.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Czech Premium Pale Lager','yeast','Soft water with low sulfate and carbonate content, Saazer\-type hops, Czech malt, Czech lager yeast. Low ion water provides a distinctively soft, rounded hop profile despite high hopping rates. The bitterness level of some larger commercial examples has dropped in recent years, although not as much as in many contemporary German examples.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dark Mild','hops','Pale British base malts \(often fairly dextrinous\), crystal malt, dark malts or dark sugar adjuncts, may also include adjuncts such as flaked maize, and may be colored with brewer\'s caramel. Characterful British ale yeast. Any type of hops, since their character is muted and rarely is noticeable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dark Mild','malt','Pale British base malts \(often fairly dextrinous\), crystal malt, dark malts or dark sugar adjuncts, may also include adjuncts such as flaked maize, and may be colored with brewer\'s caramel. Characterful British ale yeast. Any type of hops, since their character is muted and rarely is noticeable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dark Mild','sugar','Pale British base malts \(often fairly dextrinous\), crystal malt, dark malts or dark sugar adjuncts, may also include adjuncts such as flaked maize, and may be colored with brewer\'s caramel. Characterful British ale yeast. Any type of hops, since their character is muted and rarely is noticeable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dark Mild','yeast','Pale British base malts \(often fairly dextrinous\), crystal malt, dark malts or dark sugar adjuncts, may also include adjuncts such as flaked maize, and may be colored with brewer\'s caramel. Characterful British ale yeast. Any type of hops, since their character is muted and rarely is noticeable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Doppelbock','hops','Pils and/or Vienna malt for pale versions \(with some Munich\), Munich and Vienna malts for darker ones and occasionally a tiny bit of darker color malts \(such as Carafa\). Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mashing is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Doppelbock','malt','Pils and/or Vienna malt for pale versions \(with some Munich\), Munich and Vienna malts for darker ones and occasionally a tiny bit of darker color malts \(such as Carafa\). Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mashing is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Doppelbock','yeast','Pils and/or Vienna malt for pale versions \(with some Munich\), Munich and Vienna malts for darker ones and occasionally a tiny bit of darker color malts \(such as Carafa\). Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mashing is traditional.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Double IPA','hops','Clean 2\-row malt is typical as a base grain; an excessively complex grist can be distracting. Crystal\-type malts often muddy the hop flavors, and are generally considered undesirable in significant quantities. Sugar or other highly fermentable adjuncts are often used to increase attenuation, as are lower\-temperature mash rests. Can use a complex variety of hops, typically American or New World, often with cutting\-edge profiles providing distinctive differences. Modern hops with unusual characteristics are not out of style. American yeast that can give a clean or slightly fruity profile.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Double IPA','malt','Clean 2\-row malt is typical as a base grain; an excessively complex grist can be distracting. Crystal\-type malts often muddy the hop flavors, and are generally considered undesirable in significant quantities. Sugar or other highly fermentable adjuncts are often used to increase attenuation, as are lower\-temperature mash rests. Can use a complex variety of hops, typically American or New World, often with cutting\-edge profiles providing distinctive differences. Modern hops with unusual characteristics are not out of style. American yeast that can give a clean or slightly fruity profile.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Double IPA','yeast','Clean 2\-row malt is typical as a base grain; an excessively complex grist can be distracting. Crystal\-type malts often muddy the hop flavors, and are generally considered undesirable in significant quantities. Sugar or other highly fermentable adjuncts are often used to increase attenuation, as are lower\-temperature mash rests. Can use a complex variety of hops, typically American or New World, often with cutting\-edge profiles providing distinctive differences. Modern hops with unusual characteristics are not out of style. American yeast that can give a clean or slightly fruity profile.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dunkles Bock','malt','Munich and Vienna malts, rarely a tiny bit of dark roasted malts for color adjustment, never any non\-malt adjuncts. Continental European hop varieties are used. Clean German lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dunkles Bock','yeast','Munich and Vienna malts, rarely a tiny bit of dark roasted malts for color adjustment, never any non\-malt adjuncts. Continental European hop varieties are used. Clean German lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dunkles Weissbier','malt','By German brewing tradition, at least 50\% of the grist must be malted wheat, although some versions use up to 70\%; the remainder is usually Munich, Vienna, or dark or caramel wheat malts, or Pilsner malt with color malt. A decoction mash is traditional, but infrequently used today. Weizen ale yeasts produce the typical spicy and fruity character, although extreme fermentation temperatures can affect the balance and produce off\-flavors.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dunkles Weissbier','wheat','By German brewing tradition, at least 50\% of the grist must be malted wheat, although some versions use up to 70\%; the remainder is usually Munich, Vienna, or dark or caramel wheat malts, or Pilsner malt with color malt. A decoction mash is traditional, but infrequently used today. Weizen ale yeasts produce the typical spicy and fruity character, although extreme fermentation temperatures can affect the balance and produce off\-flavors.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Dunkles Weissbier','yeast','By German brewing tradition, at least 50\% of the grist must be malted wheat, although some versions use up to 70\%; the remainder is usually Munich, Vienna, or dark or caramel wheat malts, or Pilsner malt with color malt. A decoction mash is traditional, but infrequently used today. Weizen ale yeasts produce the typical spicy and fruity character, although extreme fermentation temperatures can affect the balance and produce off\-flavors.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English Barleywine','hops','High\-quality, well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist, with judicious amounts of caramel malts. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. English hops such as Northdown, Target, East Kent Goldings and Fuggles are typical. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English Barleywine','malt','High\-quality, well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist, with judicious amounts of caramel malts. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. English hops such as Northdown, Target, East Kent Goldings and Fuggles are typical. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English Barleywine','yeast','High\-quality, well\-modified pale malt should form the backbone of the grist, with judicious amounts of caramel malts. Dark malts should be used with great restraint, if at all, as most of the color arises from a lengthy boil. English hops such as Northdown, Target, East Kent Goldings and Fuggles are typical. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English IPA','hops','Pale ale malt. English hops are traditional, particularly as finishing hops. Attenuative British ale yeast. Refined sugar may be used in some versions. Some versions may show a sulfate character from Burton\-type water, but this is not essential to the style.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English IPA','malt','Pale ale malt. English hops are traditional, particularly as finishing hops. Attenuative British ale yeast. Refined sugar may be used in some versions. Some versions may show a sulfate character from Burton\-type water, but this is not essential to the style.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English IPA','sugar','Pale ale malt. English hops are traditional, particularly as finishing hops. Attenuative British ale yeast. Refined sugar may be used in some versions. Some versions may show a sulfate character from Burton\-type water, but this is not essential to the style.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English IPA','yeast','Pale ale malt. English hops are traditional, particularly as finishing hops. Attenuative British ale yeast. Refined sugar may be used in some versions. Some versions may show a sulfate character from Burton\-type water, but this is not essential to the style.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English Porter','malt','Grists vary, but something producing a dark color is always involved. Chocolate or other dark\-roasted malts, caramel malt, brewing sugars, and the like are common. London\-type porters often use brown malt as a characteristic flavor.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('English Porter','sugar','Grists vary, but something producing a dark color is always involved. Chocolate or other dark\-roasted malts, caramel malt, brewing sugars, and the like are common. London\-type porters often use brown malt as a characteristic flavor.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Festbier','malt','Majority Pils malt, but with some Vienna and/or Munich malt to increase maltiness. Differences in commercial examples are mostly due to different maltsters and yeast, not major grist differences.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Festbier','yeast','Majority Pils malt, but with some Vienna and/or Munich malt to increase maltiness. Differences in commercial examples are mostly due to different maltsters and yeast, not major grist differences.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Flanders Red Ale','hops','A base of Vienna and/or Munich malts, light to medium cara\-malts, and a small amount of Special B are used with up to 20\% maize. Low alpha acid continental hops are commonly used \(avoid high alpha or distinctive American hops\). Saccharomyces, Lactobacillus and Brettanomyces \(and acetobacter\) contribute to the fermentation and eventual flavor.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Flanders Red Ale','malt','A base of Vienna and/or Munich malts, light to medium cara\-malts, and a small amount of Special B are used with up to 20\% maize. Low alpha acid continental hops are commonly used \(avoid high alpha or distinctive American hops\). Saccharomyces, Lactobacillus and Brettanomyces \(and acetobacter\) contribute to the fermentation and eventual flavor.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Foreign Extra Stout','malt','Pale and dark roasted malts and grains, historically also could have used brown and amber malts. Hops mostly for bitterness, typically English varieties. May use adjuncts and sugar to boost gravity.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Foreign Extra Stout','sugar','Pale and dark roasted malts and grains, historically also could have used brown and amber malts. Hops mostly for bitterness, typically English varieties. May use adjuncts and sugar to boost gravity.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Fruit Lambic','hops','Unmalted wheat \(30\-40\%\), Pilsner malt and aged hops \(3 years\) are used. The aged hops are used more for preservative effects than bitterness, and makes actual bitterness levels difficult to estimate. Traditional products use 10\-30\% fruit \(25\%, if cherry\). Fruits traditionally used include tart cherries \(with pits\), raspberries or Muscat grapes. More recent examples include peaches, apricots or merlot grapes. Tart or acidic fruit is traditionally used as its purpose is not to sweeten the beer but to add a new dimension. Traditionally these beers are spontaneously fermented with naturally occurring yeast and bacteria in predominately oaken barrels. The barrels used are old and have little oak character, so don\'t expect a fresh or forward oak character – more neutral is typical. Home\-brewed and craft\-brewed versions are more typically made with pure cultures of yeast commonly including Saccharomyces, Brettanomyces, Pediococcus and Lactobacillus in an attempt to recreate the effects of the dominant microbiota of Brussels and the surrounding countryside of the Senne River valley. Cultures taken from bottles are sometimes used but there is no simple way of knowing what organisms are still viable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Fruit Lambic','malt','Unmalted wheat \(30\-40\%\), Pilsner malt and aged hops \(3 years\) are used. The aged hops are used more for preservative effects than bitterness, and makes actual bitterness levels difficult to estimate. Traditional products use 10\-30\% fruit \(25\%, if cherry\). Fruits traditionally used include tart cherries \(with pits\), raspberries or Muscat grapes. More recent examples include peaches, apricots or merlot grapes. Tart or acidic fruit is traditionally used as its purpose is not to sweeten the beer but to add a new dimension. Traditionally these beers are spontaneously fermented with naturally occurring yeast and bacteria in predominately oaken barrels. The barrels used are old and have little oak character, so don\'t expect a fresh or forward oak character – more neutral is typical. Home\-brewed and craft\-brewed versions are more typically made with pure cultures of yeast commonly including Saccharomyces, Brettanomyces, Pediococcus and Lactobacillus in an attempt to recreate the effects of the dominant microbiota of Brussels and the surrounding countryside of the Senne River valley. Cultures taken from bottles are sometimes used but there is no simple way of knowing what organisms are still viable.');
