INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Gueuze','wheat','Unmalted wheat \(30\-40\%\), Pilsner malt and aged hops \(3 years\) are used. The aged hops are used more for preservative effects than bitterness, and makes actual bitterness levels difficult to estimate. Traditionally these beers are spontaneously fermented with naturally occurring yeast and bacteria in predominately oaken barrels. The barrels used are old and have little oak character, so don\'t expect a fresh or forward oak character – more neutral is typical. Home\-brewed and craft\-brewed versions are more typically made with pure cultures of yeast commonly including Saccharomyces, Brettanomyces, Pediococcus and Lactobacillus in an attempt to recreate the effects of the dominant microbiota of Brussels and the surrounding countryside of the Senne River valley. Cultures taken from bottles are sometimes used but there is no simple way of knowing what organisms are still viable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Gueuze','yeast','Unmalted wheat \(30\-40\%\), Pilsner malt and aged hops \(3 years\) are used. The aged hops are used more for preservative effects than bitterness, and makes actual bitterness levels difficult to estimate. Traditionally these beers are spontaneously fermented with naturally occurring yeast and bacteria in predominately oaken barrels. The barrels used are old and have little oak character, so don\'t expect a fresh or forward oak character – more neutral is typical. Home\-brewed and craft\-brewed versions are more typically made with pure cultures of yeast commonly including Saccharomyces, Brettanomyces, Pediococcus and Lactobacillus in an attempt to recreate the effects of the dominant microbiota of Brussels and the surrounding countryside of the Senne River valley. Cultures taken from bottles are sometimes used but there is no simple way of knowing what organisms are still viable.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Helles Bock','hops','Base of Pils and/or Vienna malt with some Munich malt to add character \(although much less than in a traditional bock\). No non\-malt adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mash is typical, but boiling is less than in Dunkles Bock to restrain color development.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Helles Bock','malt','Base of Pils and/or Vienna malt with some Munich malt to add character \(although much less than in a traditional bock\). No non\-malt adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mash is typical, but boiling is less than in Dunkles Bock to restrain color development.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Helles Bock','yeast','Base of Pils and/or Vienna malt with some Munich malt to add character \(although much less than in a traditional bock\). No non\-malt adjuncts. Saazer\-type hops. Clean lager yeast. Decoction mash is typical, but boiling is less than in Dunkles Bock to restrain color development.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Imperial Stout','hops','Well\-modified pale malt, with generous quantities of roasted malts and/or grain. May have a complex grain bill using virtually any variety of malt. Any type of hops may be used. American or English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Imperial Stout','malt','Well\-modified pale malt, with generous quantities of roasted malts and/or grain. May have a complex grain bill using virtually any variety of malt. Any type of hops may be used. American or English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Imperial Stout','yeast','Well\-modified pale malt, with generous quantities of roasted malts and/or grain. May have a complex grain bill using virtually any variety of malt. Any type of hops may be used. American or English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Amber Lager','hops','Two\-row or six\-row base malt. Color malts such as victory, amber, etc. Caramel malt adjuncts. European or American hops or a combination of both.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Amber Lager','malt','Two\-row or six\-row base malt. Color malts such as victory, amber, etc. Caramel malt adjuncts. European or American hops or a combination of both.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Dark Lager','corn','Two\- or six\-row barley, corn, rice, or sugars as adjuncts. Light use of caramel and darker malts. Commercial versions may use coloring agents.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Dark Lager','malt','Two\- or six\-row barley, corn, rice, or sugars as adjuncts. Light use of caramel and darker malts. Commercial versions may use coloring agents.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Dark Lager','rice','Two\- or six\-row barley, corn, rice, or sugars as adjuncts. Light use of caramel and darker malts. Commercial versions may use coloring agents.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Dark Lager','six\-row barley','Two\- or six\-row barley, corn, rice, or sugars as adjuncts. Light use of caramel and darker malts. Commercial versions may use coloring agents.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Dark Lager','sugar','Two\- or six\-row barley, corn, rice, or sugars as adjuncts. Light use of caramel and darker malts. Commercial versions may use coloring agents.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Pale Lager','corn','Two\- or six\-row barley. May use rice, corn, or sugar as adjuncts, or may be all malt.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Pale Lager','malt','Two\- or six\-row barley. May use rice, corn, or sugar as adjuncts, or may be all malt.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Pale Lager','rice','Two\- or six\-row barley. May use rice, corn, or sugar as adjuncts, or may be all malt.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Pale Lager','six\-row barley','Two\- or six\-row barley. May use rice, corn, or sugar as adjuncts, or may be all malt.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('International Pale Lager','sugar','Two\- or six\-row barley. May use rice, corn, or sugar as adjuncts, or may be all malt.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Irish Red Ale','malt','Generally has a bit of roasted barley or black malt to provide reddish color and dry roasted finish. Pale base malt. Caramel malts were historically imported and more expensive, so not all brewers would use them.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Irish Stout','malt','Guinness is made using roasted barley, flaked barley, and pale malt, but other breweries don\'t necessarily use roasted barley; they can use chocolate or other dark and specialty malts. Whatever combination of malts or grains is used, the resulting product should be black. Cork\-type stouts are perhaps closer to historical London\-type stouts in composition with a varied grist not dominated by roasted barley.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Kellerbier','hops','Grist varies, although traditional German versions emphasized Franconian pale and color malt. The notion of elegance is derived from the high\-quality local ingredients, particularly the malts. Spalt or other typically spicy local hops are most common. Frugal Franconian brewers rarely used decoction brewing due to the cost of energy.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Kellerbier','malt','Grist varies, although traditional German versions emphasized Franconian pale and color malt. The notion of elegance is derived from the high\-quality local ingredients, particularly the malts. Spalt or other typically spicy local hops are most common. Frugal Franconian brewers rarely used decoction brewing due to the cost of energy.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Kentucky Common','corn','Six\-row barley malt was used with 35\% corn grits to dilute the excessive protein levels along with 1 to 2\% each caramel and black malt. Native American hops, usually about .2 pounds per barrel of Western hops for bittering and a similar amount of New York hops \(such as Clusters\) for flavor \(15 minutes prior to knock out\). Imported continental Saazer\-type hops \(.1 pounds per barrel\) were added at knock out for aroma. Water in the Louisville area was typically moderate to high in carbonates. Mash water was often pre\-boiled to precipitate the carbonate and Gypsum was commonly added. Considering the time from mash in to kegging for delivery was typically 6 to 8 days, clearly aggressive top\-fermenting yeasts was used.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Kentucky Common','hops','Six\-row barley malt was used with 35\% corn grits to dilute the excessive protein levels along with 1 to 2\% each caramel and black malt. Native American hops, usually about .2 pounds per barrel of Western hops for bittering and a similar amount of New York hops \(such as Clusters\) for flavor \(15 minutes prior to knock out\). Imported continental Saazer\-type hops \(.1 pounds per barrel\) were added at knock out for aroma. Water in the Louisville area was typically moderate to high in carbonates. Mash water was often pre\-boiled to precipitate the carbonate and Gypsum was commonly added. Considering the time from mash in to kegging for delivery was typically 6 to 8 days, clearly aggressive top\-fermenting yeasts was used.');
