INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Lichtenhainer','malt','Smoked barley malt, wheat malt, lactobacillus, top\-fermenting yeast. Grists vary, but the wheat would typically be 30\-50\%.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Lichtenhainer','wheat','Smoked barley malt, wheat malt, lactobacillus, top\-fermenting yeast. Grists vary, but the wheat would typically be 30\-50\%.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Lichtenhainer','yeast','Smoked barley malt, wheat malt, lactobacillus, top\-fermenting yeast. Grists vary, but the wheat would typically be 30\-50\%.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('London Brown Ale','malt','English pale ale malt as a base with a healthy proportion of darker caramel malts and often some roasted \(black\) malt and wheat malt \(this is Mann\'s traditional grist – others can rely on dark sugars for color and flavor\). Moderate to high carbonate water. English hop varieties are most authentic, though with low flavor and bitterness almost any type could be used. Post\-fermentation sweetening with lactose or artificial sweeteners, or sucrose \(if pasteurized\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('London Brown Ale','sugar','English pale ale malt as a base with a healthy proportion of darker caramel malts and often some roasted \(black\) malt and wheat malt \(this is Mann\'s traditional grist – others can rely on dark sugars for color and flavor\). Moderate to high carbonate water. English hop varieties are most authentic, though with low flavor and bitterness almost any type could be used. Post\-fermentation sweetening with lactose or artificial sweeteners, or sucrose \(if pasteurized\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('London Brown Ale','wheat','English pale ale malt as a base with a healthy proportion of darker caramel malts and often some roasted \(black\) malt and wheat malt \(this is Mann\'s traditional grist – others can rely on dark sugars for color and flavor\). Moderate to high carbonate water. English hop varieties are most authentic, though with low flavor and bitterness almost any type could be used. Post\-fermentation sweetening with lactose or artificial sweeteners, or sucrose \(if pasteurized\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Munich Dunkel','malt','Grist is traditionally made up of German Munich malt \(up to 100\% in some cases\) with the remainder German Pilsner malt. Small amounts of crystal malt can add dextrins and color but should not introduce excessive residual sweetness. Slight additions of roasted malts \(such as Carafa or chocolate\) may be used to improve color but should not add strong flavors. Traditional German hop varieties and German lager yeast strains should be used. Often decoction mashed \(up to a triple decoction\) to enhance the malt flavors and create the depth of color.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Munich Dunkel','yeast','Grist is traditionally made up of German Munich malt \(up to 100\% in some cases\) with the remainder German Pilsner malt. Small amounts of crystal malt can add dextrins and color but should not introduce excessive residual sweetness. Slight additions of roasted malts \(such as Carafa or chocolate\) may be used to improve color but should not add strong flavors. Traditional German hop varieties and German lager yeast strains should be used. Often decoction mashed \(up to a triple decoction\) to enhance the malt flavors and create the depth of color.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Munich Helles','malt','Continental Pilsner malt, traditional German Saazer\-type hop varieties, clean German lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Munich Helles','yeast','Continental Pilsner malt, traditional German Saazer\-type hop varieties, clean German lager yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Märzen','malt','Grist varies, although traditional German versions emphasized Munich malt. The notion of elegance is derived from the finest quality ingredients, particularly the base malts. A decoction mash was traditionally used to develop the rich malt profile.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oatmeal Stout','Oat','Pale, caramel and dark roasted malts \(often chocolate\) and grains. Oatmeal or malted oats \(5\-20\% or more\) used to enhance fullness of body and complexity of flavor. Hops primarily for bittering. Can use brewing sugars or syrups. English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oatmeal Stout','malt','Pale, caramel and dark roasted malts \(often chocolate\) and grains. Oatmeal or malted oats \(5\-20\% or more\) used to enhance fullness of body and complexity of flavor. Hops primarily for bittering. Can use brewing sugars or syrups. English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oatmeal Stout','sugar','Pale, caramel and dark roasted malts \(often chocolate\) and grains. Oatmeal or malted oats \(5\-20\% or more\) used to enhance fullness of body and complexity of flavor. Hops primarily for bittering. Can use brewing sugars or syrups. English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oatmeal Stout','yeast','Pale, caramel and dark roasted malts \(often chocolate\) and grains. Oatmeal or malted oats \(5\-20\% or more\) used to enhance fullness of body and complexity of flavor. Hops primarily for bittering. Can use brewing sugars or syrups. English ale yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','corn','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','hops','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','malt','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','sugar','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','wheat','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Ordinary Bitter','yeast','Pale ale, amber, and/or crystal malts. May use a touch of dark malt for color adjustment. May use sugar adjuncts, corn, or wheat. English finishing hops are most traditional, but any hops are fair game; if American hops are used, a light touch is required. Characterful British yeast.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oud Bruin','hops','A base of Pils malt with judicious amounts of dark cara malts and a tiny bit of black or roast malt. Often includes maize. Low alpha acid continental hops are typical \(avoid high alpha or distinctive American hops\). Saccharomyces and Lactobacillus \(and acetobacter\) contribute to the fermentation and eventual flavor. Lactobacillus reacts poorly to elevated levels of alcohol. Water high in carbonates is typical of its home region and will buffer the acidity of darker malts and the lactic sourness. Magnesium in the water accentuates the sourness.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Oud Bruin','malt','A base of Pils malt with judicious amounts of dark cara malts and a tiny bit of black or roast malt. Often includes maize. Low alpha acid continental hops are typical \(avoid high alpha or distinctive American hops\). Saccharomyces and Lactobacillus \(and acetobacter\) contribute to the fermentation and eventual flavor. Lactobacillus reacts poorly to elevated levels of alcohol. Water high in carbonates is typical of its home region and will buffer the acidity of darker malts and the lactic sourness. Magnesium in the water accentuates the sourness.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Piwo Grodziskie','hops','Grain bill usually consists entirely of oak\-smoked wheat malt. Oak\-smoked wheat malt has a different \(and less intense\) smoke character than German beechwood\-smoked barley malt; it has a drier, crisper, leaner quality – a bacon/ham smoke flavor is inappropriate. Saazer\-type hops \(Polish, Czech or German\), moderate hardness sulfate water, and a relatively clean and attenuative continental ale yeast fermented at moderate ale temperatures are traditional. German hefeweizen yeast or other strains with a phenol or strong ester character are inappropriate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Piwo Grodziskie','malt','Grain bill usually consists entirely of oak\-smoked wheat malt. Oak\-smoked wheat malt has a different \(and less intense\) smoke character than German beechwood\-smoked barley malt; it has a drier, crisper, leaner quality – a bacon/ham smoke flavor is inappropriate. Saazer\-type hops \(Polish, Czech or German\), moderate hardness sulfate water, and a relatively clean and attenuative continental ale yeast fermented at moderate ale temperatures are traditional. German hefeweizen yeast or other strains with a phenol or strong ester character are inappropriate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Piwo Grodziskie','wheat','Grain bill usually consists entirely of oak\-smoked wheat malt. Oak\-smoked wheat malt has a different \(and less intense\) smoke character than German beechwood\-smoked barley malt; it has a drier, crisper, leaner quality – a bacon/ham smoke flavor is inappropriate. Saazer\-type hops \(Polish, Czech or German\), moderate hardness sulfate water, and a relatively clean and attenuative continental ale yeast fermented at moderate ale temperatures are traditional. German hefeweizen yeast or other strains with a phenol or strong ester character are inappropriate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Piwo Grodziskie','yeast','Grain bill usually consists entirely of oak\-smoked wheat malt. Oak\-smoked wheat malt has a different \(and less intense\) smoke character than German beechwood\-smoked barley malt; it has a drier, crisper, leaner quality – a bacon/ham smoke flavor is inappropriate. Saazer\-type hops \(Polish, Czech or German\), moderate hardness sulfate water, and a relatively clean and attenuative continental ale yeast fermented at moderate ale temperatures are traditional. German hefeweizen yeast or other strains with a phenol or strong ester character are inappropriate.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Lager','corn','Six\-row barley with 20\% to 30\% flaked maize \(corn\) or rice to dilute the excessive protein levels; modern versions may be all malt. Native American hops such as Clusters, traditional continental hops, or modern noble\-type crosses are also appropriate. Modern American hops such as Cascade are inappropriate. Water with a high mineral content can lead to an unpleasant coarseness in flavor and harshness in aftertaste. A wide range of lager yeast character can be exhibited, although modern versions tend to be fairly clean.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Lager','hops','Six\-row barley with 20\% to 30\% flaked maize \(corn\) or rice to dilute the excessive protein levels; modern versions may be all malt. Native American hops such as Clusters, traditional continental hops, or modern noble\-type crosses are also appropriate. Modern American hops such as Cascade are inappropriate. Water with a high mineral content can lead to an unpleasant coarseness in flavor and harshness in aftertaste. A wide range of lager yeast character can be exhibited, although modern versions tend to be fairly clean.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Lager','malt','Six\-row barley with 20\% to 30\% flaked maize \(corn\) or rice to dilute the excessive protein levels; modern versions may be all malt. Native American hops such as Clusters, traditional continental hops, or modern noble\-type crosses are also appropriate. Modern American hops such as Cascade are inappropriate. Water with a high mineral content can lead to an unpleasant coarseness in flavor and harshness in aftertaste. A wide range of lager yeast character can be exhibited, although modern versions tend to be fairly clean.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Lager','rice','Six\-row barley with 20\% to 30\% flaked maize \(corn\) or rice to dilute the excessive protein levels; modern versions may be all malt. Native American hops such as Clusters, traditional continental hops, or modern noble\-type crosses are also appropriate. Modern American hops such as Cascade are inappropriate. Water with a high mineral content can lead to an unpleasant coarseness in flavor and harshness in aftertaste. A wide range of lager yeast character can be exhibited, although modern versions tend to be fairly clean.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Lager','yeast','Six\-row barley with 20\% to 30\% flaked maize \(corn\) or rice to dilute the excessive protein levels; modern versions may be all malt. Native American hops such as Clusters, traditional continental hops, or modern noble\-type crosses are also appropriate. Modern American hops such as Cascade are inappropriate. Water with a high mineral content can lead to an unpleasant coarseness in flavor and harshness in aftertaste. A wide range of lager yeast character can be exhibited, although modern versions tend to be fairly clean.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Porter','corn','Two and six row malt \(or a combination of both\) are used, along with low percentages of dark malts including black, chocolate, and brown malt \(roasted barley is not typically used\). Adjuncts are acceptable, including corn, brewers licorice, molasses, and porterine. More historical versions will have up to twenty percent adjuncts. Lager or ale yeast. Emphasis on historical or traditional American bittering hops \(Cluster, Willamette, Cascade\), though finishing and flavor hops may vary.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Porter','hops','Two and six row malt \(or a combination of both\) are used, along with low percentages of dark malts including black, chocolate, and brown malt \(roasted barley is not typically used\). Adjuncts are acceptable, including corn, brewers licorice, molasses, and porterine. More historical versions will have up to twenty percent adjuncts. Lager or ale yeast. Emphasis on historical or traditional American bittering hops \(Cluster, Willamette, Cascade\), though finishing and flavor hops may vary.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Porter','malt','Two and six row malt \(or a combination of both\) are used, along with low percentages of dark malts including black, chocolate, and brown malt \(roasted barley is not typically used\). Adjuncts are acceptable, including corn, brewers licorice, molasses, and porterine. More historical versions will have up to twenty percent adjuncts. Lager or ale yeast. Emphasis on historical or traditional American bittering hops \(Cluster, Willamette, Cascade\), though finishing and flavor hops may vary.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Porter','rice','Two and six row malt \(or a combination of both\) are used, along with low percentages of dark malts including black, chocolate, and brown malt \(roasted barley is not typically used\). Adjuncts are acceptable, including corn, brewers licorice, molasses, and porterine. More historical versions will have up to twenty percent adjuncts. Lager or ale yeast. Emphasis on historical or traditional American bittering hops \(Cluster, Willamette, Cascade\), though finishing and flavor hops may vary.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Pre\-Prohibition Porter','yeast','Two and six row malt \(or a combination of both\) are used, along with low percentages of dark malts including black, chocolate, and brown malt \(roasted barley is not typically used\). Adjuncts are acceptable, including corn, brewers licorice, molasses, and porterine. More historical versions will have up to twenty percent adjuncts. Lager or ale yeast. Emphasis on historical or traditional American bittering hops \(Cluster, Willamette, Cascade\), though finishing and flavor hops may vary.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Rauchbier','hops','German Rauchmalz \(beechwood\-smoked Vienna\-type malt\) typically makes up 20\-100\% of the grain bill, with the remainder being German malts typically used in a Märzen. Some breweries adjust the color slightly with a bit of roasted malt. German lager yeast. German or Czech hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Rauchbier','malt','German Rauchmalz \(beechwood\-smoked Vienna\-type malt\) typically makes up 20\-100\% of the grain bill, with the remainder being German malts typically used in a Märzen. Some breweries adjust the color slightly with a bit of roasted malt. German lager yeast. German or Czech hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Rauchbier','yeast','German Rauchmalz \(beechwood\-smoked Vienna\-type malt\) typically makes up 20\-100\% of the grain bill, with the remainder being German malts typically used in a Märzen. Some breweries adjust the color slightly with a bit of roasted malt. German lager yeast. German or Czech hops.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Roggenbier','hops','Malted rye typically constitutes 50\% or greater of the grist \(some versions have 60\-65\% rye\). Remainder of grist can include pale malt, Munich malt, wheat malt, crystal malt and/or small amounts of debittered dark malts for color adjustment. Weizen yeast provides distinctive banana esters and clove phenols. Light usage of Saazer\-type hops in bitterness, flavor and aroma. Lower fermentation temperatures accentuate the clove character by suppressing ester formation. Decoction mash traditionally used \(as with weissbiers\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Roggenbier','malt','Malted rye typically constitutes 50\% or greater of the grist \(some versions have 60\-65\% rye\). Remainder of grist can include pale malt, Munich malt, wheat malt, crystal malt and/or small amounts of debittered dark malts for color adjustment. Weizen yeast provides distinctive banana esters and clove phenols. Light usage of Saazer\-type hops in bitterness, flavor and aroma. Lower fermentation temperatures accentuate the clove character by suppressing ester formation. Decoction mash traditionally used \(as with weissbiers\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Roggenbier','wheat','Malted rye typically constitutes 50\% or greater of the grist \(some versions have 60\-65\% rye\). Remainder of grist can include pale malt, Munich malt, wheat malt, crystal malt and/or small amounts of debittered dark malts for color adjustment. Weizen yeast provides distinctive banana esters and clove phenols. Light usage of Saazer\-type hops in bitterness, flavor and aroma. Lower fermentation temperatures accentuate the clove character by suppressing ester formation. Decoction mash traditionally used \(as with weissbiers\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Roggenbier','yeast','Malted rye typically constitutes 50\% or greater of the grist \(some versions have 60\-65\% rye\). Remainder of grist can include pale malt, Munich malt, wheat malt, crystal malt and/or small amounts of debittered dark malts for color adjustment. Weizen yeast provides distinctive banana esters and clove phenols. Light usage of Saazer\-type hops in bitterness, flavor and aroma. Lower fermentation temperatures accentuate the clove character by suppressing ester formation. Decoction mash traditionally used \(as with weissbiers\).');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Sahti','hops','Malted barley along with malted and unmalted grains, often rye. Low hops. Juniper boughs used for lautering \(traditionally in a hollowed\-out log\), but often producing a juniper/berry character. Often uses top\-fermenting baker\'s yeast in a fast, warm fermentation \(German Weizen yeast is a good substitute\). Not boiled; a long mash steep is used, with a separately added hop tea.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Sahti','malt','Malted barley along with malted and unmalted grains, often rye. Low hops. Juniper boughs used for lautering \(traditionally in a hollowed\-out log\), but often producing a juniper/berry character. Often uses top\-fermenting baker\'s yeast in a fast, warm fermentation \(German Weizen yeast is a good substitute\). Not boiled; a long mash steep is used, with a separately added hop tea.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Sahti','yeast','Malted barley along with malted and unmalted grains, often rye. Low hops. Juniper boughs used for lautering \(traditionally in a hollowed\-out log\), but often producing a juniper/berry character. Often uses top\-fermenting baker\'s yeast in a fast, warm fermentation \(German Weizen yeast is a good substitute\). Not boiled; a long mash steep is used, with a separately added hop tea.');
INSERT INTO characteristic_ingredient VALUES ('Saison','hops','Not typically spiced, with the yeast, hops and grain providing the character; but spices are allowed if they provide a complementary character. Continental base malts are typical, but the grist frequently contains other grains such as wheat, oats, rye, or spelt. Adjuncts such as sugar and honey can also serve to add complexity and dry out the beer. Darker versions will typically use richer, darker malts, but not typically roasted types. Saazer\-type, Styrian or East Kent Golding hops are commonly used. A wide range of herbs or spices can add complexity and uniqueness, but should always meld well with the yeast and hop character. Brettanomyces is not typical for this style; Saisons with Brett should be entered in the American Wild Ale category.');
